  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Project Engineer ACMV /HAVC",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles & Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>To engage in project engineering of ACMV Systems.</li><li>Responsible for planning, scheduling, forecasting, conducting and coordinating the technical and management aspects of projects.</li><li>To lead and communicate with our Site Engineer and Site Supervisor.</li><li>Controlling the cost of the materials and labour.</li><li>Attend site meeting, inspection and monitoring of project progress.</li><li>Liaising and coordinating with all parties involved in the projects such as consultants, main contractors, sub-contractors, suppliers, local authorities, environmental agencies and federal entities etc to ensure successful implementation of the project.</li><li>Ensure that all the construction safety rules and regulations are being observed.</li><li>Scheduling the construction work of the day.</li><li>Laying down the preferred construction methods.</li><li>Ensure proper project documentation.</li><li>Monitor and report project progression to management.</li><li>Any other tasks assigned by the management.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Min. Degree in Mechanical Engineering or its equivalent</li><li>With Electrical Background will be a plus.</li><li>Min. 3 years of experience in ACMV works.</li><li>Must have Singapore Class 3 Driving License.</li><li>A team player and possess problem-solving, coordination and management skills.</li><li>Able to work independently and work as a project team</li><li>Able to carry out prescribed work in a safe, competent or compliant matter.</li><li>Possession of outstanding written and verbal communication skills, as well as having strong interpersonal skills</li><li>Self-motivated individual, with phenomenal confidence working with diverse partner groups</li><li>Able to perform using AutoCad and other drawing applications</li><li>Knowledge in AutoCAD drawings</li><li>Good team player and handle stress and deadlines.</li></ul><ul><li>We offer attractive remuneration package to the right candidate.</li><li>Company Vehicle provided. (Singapore Class 3 Driving License required) </li><li>Interested candidates are invited to submit detailed resume stating:-</li><li><strong>Current salary;</strong></li><li><strong>Expected salary;</strong></li><li><strong>Reasons of leaving and</strong></li><li><strong>Date of availability.</strong></li></ul><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>",
